description: Try our easy to follow Stuffed Zucchini In Tomato Sauce recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
keywords: Stuffed vegetable,Zucchini,Roast,Seafood free,Christmas,Wheat free,Gluten free,Rice,Egg free,Sesame free
name: Stuffed Zucchini In Tomato Sauce Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 0.25 cup mint, finely chopped (plus extra leaves to serve)
1 tbs ras el hanout (or moroccan seasoning)

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 220Â°C. Line a roasting pan with baking paper. Halve zucchini lengthways and pat dry. Arrange, cut-side up, in pan. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle with ras el hanout and season. Loosely wrap onion in foil and add to pan. Place pan in oven and bake for 15 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.

Transfer zucchini to a chopping board and use a teaspoon to scrape out zucchini flesh, leaving a shell. Roughly chop flesh and combine with onion, rice mixture, chopped mint and pine nuts. Season and mix well.
Pour tomatoes in pan and roughly squash with a fork. Return zucchini to roasting pan. Fill with rice mixture and scatter over feta.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown on top. Garnish with extra mint and serve.
